The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves integrating relative spatial information into global features, which is a technique that can be applied to various machine learning tasks such as classification and clustering, hence it could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which is a popular subfield of computer vision and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves the use of tensors, which is a mathematical concept that is often used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
